HEADWORD: Kilogramme
<hw>Kil"o*gramme</hw> }</mhw>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>kilogramme</ets>; pref. <ets>kilo-</ets>
(fr. Gr. <grk>chi`lioi</grk> a thousand ) + <ets>gramme.</ets> See 3d
<er>Gram</er>.]</ety> <def>A measure of mass and weight, being a
thousand grams, equal to 2.2046226 pounds avoirdupois (15,432.34
grains). It is nearly equal to the mass of a cubic decimeter of
distilled water at the temperature of maximum density, or 39⟦deg⟧
Fahrenheit. See 3rd <er>gram</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

